<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693601>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 164. Distribution map of Platycheirus species in Chile: Platycheirus (Carposcalis) chalconotus (Philippi, 1865) (blue circles); Platycheirus (Carposcalis) fenestratus (Macquart, 1842) (red circles); Platycheirus (Carposcalis) punctulatum (Wulp, 1888) (black circles); Platycheirus (Carposcalis) lundbladi (Enderlain, 1940) (green circles) and Paragus angustistylus Vockeroth, 1968 (yellow triangle)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4693601/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693598>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 158–163. Platycheirus (Carposcalis) chalconotus (Philippi, 1865): (158) female in Amsinckia calycina (Moris) Chater (photo by Matías Cortés); (159) male extending the proboscis (photo by Gabriela Germain); (160) male resting (photo by Diego Gutiérrez). Platycheirus (Carposcalis) fenestratus (Macquart, 1842): (161) female, dorsal habitus (photo: Patricia Henríquez), scale bar = 1 mm; (162) female resting (photo by Matías Cortés) and (163) male resting (Photo by Gabriela Germain)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4693598/files/figure.png" .

